#: 6e5b540253cb4590aead120f4276934f
msgid "Modifying the AOI search"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:247
#: 06050ad4c40442209f3ac3963c664609
msgid ""
"You can add a new AOI to an existing search, modify the geometry, or "
"delete areas that have already been processed. After any AOI changes, you"
" will need to confirm these changes. The search will be updated, and the "
"**results will be synchronized** accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: 778bba647e3c49f2b9e3551fb529451f
msgid "Update template"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:257
#: 4d5fa1464af54a88aa614dd1a282e9db
msgid "**You can also change the search criteria for the existing search:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:259
#: edc2ed2d4b5c46539f1297ea12560b44
msgid ""
"\"View on the map\" → Adjust the search parameters → \"Search Imagery\" →"
" \"Save as schedule\". Now the background search will work according to "
"the new parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:270
#: 0e1cd010b3fb4e19941fd292f364f886
msgid "Using Mapflow Imagery Search in QGIS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:272
#: beb2801ebc0244058db6c79d32c1679a
msgid ""
"Switch to the tab \"Imagery Search\". To start the search, set the dates "
"and the product type filters (\"Mosaic\" – Imagery basemaps like ArcGIS "
"or Global mosaic and/or \"Images\" - Satellite imagery archives)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:273
#: 6b3c61b5f88a4cb0bd286b719e0ba1fb
msgid ""
"Set additional filters like a minimum intersection with your area of "
"analysis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:274
#: ba9e87331e3a4d828b54dae7776e3904
msgid ""
"If there is non-empty response, it will add the **🔎 Imagery Search "
"metadata** layer to your QGIS project. You can select one or multiple "
"results in the table - or use the layer's attribute table to start the "
"analysis and processing with Mapflow models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/imagery_search.rst:283
#: d6e2d4100d8440dc8b1fd1ad910830ab
msgid ""
"In the Arcgis search results you see the zoom level at which the mosaic "
"is available over you area. You can configure the table columns in the "
"Settings."
msgstr ""

